text: Kristinestad () is a town in the Ostrobothia region of Finland. There were about 7,000 people living there in January 2014. It is next to the municipalities of Isojoki, Karijoki, Merikarvia, NÃ¤rpes and Teuva. The people living in the town are bilingual; about 56% of the people speak Swedish.
